246
00:15:47,781 --> 00:15:51,718
>>This is a long time ago...

247
00:15:51,785 --> 00:15:57,223
When Kamiki was there, a certain employee was fired.

248
00:15:57,290 --> 00:16:01,227
This really shouldn't happen →

249
00:16:01,294 --> 00:16:05,732
He was violent towards children.

250
00:16:05,799 --> 00:16:10,236
The one who showed me the evidence and accused me →

251
00:16:10,303 --> 00:16:13,239
It was Kamiki-kun.

252
00:16:13,306 --> 00:16:16,242
I was probably around 10 years old or so.

253
00:16:16,309 --> 00:16:19,746
(Kuroiwa) That's all I got at 10 years old.

254
00:16:19,813 --> 00:16:22,749
>> I found out later →

255
00:16:22,816 --> 00:16:26,753
Some of the evidence was fabricated.

256
00:16:26,820 --> 00:16:28,822
(Kuroiwa) Huh?

257
00:16:33,927 --> 00:16:36,496
(footsteps)

258
00:16:36,563 --> 00:16:38,998
(Tanaka) Today was amazing.

259
00:16:39,065 --> 00:16:41,501
(Manami) Is that so? >> Did something happen?

260
00:16:42,168 --> 00:16:43,970
(Manami) Maybe it's because it's been a while.

261
00:16:44,037 --> 00:16:45,972
I can do it three more times!

262
00:16:46,039 --> 00:16:49,042
>> I'm at my limit. (Manami) Haha Yes...

263
00:16:52,045 --> 00:17:04,424
♪～

264
00:17:04,491 --> 00:17:06,426
(Kamiki) Mr. Kuroiwa.

265
00:17:06,493 --> 00:17:08,428
(Kuroiwa) Yes.

266
00:17:08,495 --> 00:17:12,932
>> What do you like about Manami Tanizaki?

267
00:17:13,299 --> 00:17:15,235
(Kuroiwa) Yes?

268
00:17:15,301 --> 00:17:18,238
>>You don't have to be me to understand.

269
00:17:18,304 --> 00:17:20,740
How do you feel?

270
00:17:20,807 --> 00:17:25,311
What is it? That person is strange.

271
00:17:26,813 --> 00:17:30,750
I don’t think I can leave it alone →

272
00:17:30,817 --> 00:17:33,820
I also want you to live as you please.

273
00:17:36,322 --> 00:17:39,759
If it’s for that person→

274
00:17:39,826 --> 00:17:43,329
It seems like anything is possible.

275
00:17:47,333 --> 00:17:49,836
(Sound of file closing)

276
00:17:57,277 --> 00:18:00,713
What happened to Mr. Takamine?

277
00:18:00,780 --> 00:18:03,716
(Manami) You were right.

278
00:18:03,783 --> 00:18:08,221
>> I have a theory regarding Mr. Takamine.

279
00:18:08,288 --> 00:18:10,223
(Manami) Hypothesis?

280
00:18:10,290 --> 00:18:12,225
>> [Manami Tanizaki!!]

281
00:18:12,292 --> 00:18:14,727
(Kamiki's voice) When they first interrogated me →

282
00:18:14,794 --> 00:18:17,730
It seemed like she had a fear of men.

283
00:18:17,797 --> 00:18:21,234
Some of my patients are like that →

284
00:18:21,301 --> 00:18:23,736
Sexual crimes such as molestation →

285
00:18:23,803 --> 00:18:27,240
There are many cases of people suffering from stalking.

286
00:18:27,307 --> 00:18:31,744
I'm very worried.

287
00:18:31,811 --> 00:18:34,247
(Kuroiwa) Did you do that from the beginning?

288
00:18:34,314 --> 00:18:38,818
>> Good, I was able to protect you again.

289
00:18:42,322 --> 00:18:45,258
(Manami) What is it? >> Yes?

290
00:18:45,325 --> 00:18:50,263
(Manami) You're trying to help me like this.

291
00:18:50,330 --> 00:18:54,701
There's no point in doing it if you're trying to atone for your sins.

292
00:18:54,767 --> 00:19:00,206
>> I've always been trying to help you.

293
00:19:00,273 --> 00:19:03,776
(Kuroiwa) There is no point if you do it wrong.

294
00:19:05,278 --> 00:19:09,215
I spoke to you at the facility where you grew up.

295
00:19:09,282 --> 00:19:15,288
>> Ah, did you go there?

296
00:19:17,790 --> 00:19:20,226
It's a bit easy.

297
00:19:20,293 --> 00:19:23,229
Do you need a cause that much?

298
00:19:23,296 --> 00:19:26,733
I keep saying that.

299
00:19:26,799 --> 00:19:29,736
Even if there is no convincing reason →

300
00:19:29,802 --> 00:19:32,739
It suddenly turns over.

301
00:19:32,805 --> 00:19:35,742
Well, I understand how you feel.

302
00:19:35,808 --> 00:19:39,746
Because I'm an orphan, I'm lonely and my heart is warped.

303
00:19:39,812 --> 00:19:41,748
I committed a crime.

304
00:19:41,814 --> 00:19:44,751
It's a common and plausible explanation.

305
00:19:44,817 --> 00:19:48,254
(Kuroiwa) No, that's not my intention... >> But...

306
00:19:48,321 --> 00:19:52,258
It's a bit lenient!

307
00:19:52,325 --> 00:19:54,694
(Kuroiwa) How to gouge?

308
00:19:54,761 --> 00:19:57,263
>> I'll try it now.

309
00:20:04,771 --> 00:20:09,709
When did you lose the confidence to love one person?

310
00:20:09,776 --> 00:20:15,281
During childhood, adolescence, or after breaking up with Kiryu-san?

311
00:20:17,283 --> 00:20:21,287
Record! Take it.

312
00:20:23,790 --> 00:20:25,725
(Manami) Why are you... >> Because I'm not confident →

313
00:20:25,792 --> 00:20:28,728
Fall in love with all kinds of people!

314
00:20:28,795 --> 00:20:32,732
I'm lonely so I decided to go to a nursing home →

315
00:20:32,799 --> 00:20:35,735
I'm trying to close my life.

316
00:20:35,802 --> 00:20:40,239
Even though there are many of them, I truly love each and every one of them.

317
00:20:40,306 --> 00:20:46,246
But people rarely understand that.

318
00:20:46,312 --> 00:20:50,249
Unnecessary things are said.

319
00:20:50,316 --> 00:20:55,188
“That’s not normal!”

320
00:20:55,255 --> 00:20:58,691
"I can't be happy."

321
00:20:58,758 --> 00:21:06,199
And now... my loved ones are being killed one after another.

322
00:21:06,265 --> 00:21:08,701
Every time someone gets killed →

323
00:21:08,768 --> 00:21:11,204
Even though I'm about to be torn apart →

324
00:21:11,270 --> 00:21:13,706
The sadness seems light.

325
00:21:13,773 --> 00:21:15,708
Because there are many.

326
00:21:15,775 --> 00:21:19,212
It is strange to even cry for them.

327
00:21:19,278 --> 00:21:22,281
Your loneliness only deepens.

328
00:21:24,284 --> 00:21:26,219
(Manami) That's enough.

329
00:21:26,285 --> 00:21:31,224
>>Even if you can't fill that loneliness→

330
00:21:31,290 --> 00:21:34,794
I can do it as long as you support me.

331
00:21:36,796 --> 00:21:42,735
I... I won't leave you.

332
00:21:42,802 --> 00:21:48,241
♪～

333
00:21:48,307 --> 00:21:50,810
You...

334
00:21:53,246 --> 00:21:55,748
I want to help.

335
00:22:01,254 --> 00:22:05,692
(Manami) That's enough. >> It suits you.

336
00:22:05,758 --> 00:22:07,694
(Manami) Huh?

337
00:22:07,760 --> 00:22:09,762
>>That hair.

338
00:22:16,269 --> 00:22:18,705
If you want to gouge someone's heart →

339
00:22:18,771 --> 00:22:21,207
I have to do this much.

340
00:22:21,274 --> 00:22:33,219
♪～

341
00:22:33,286 --> 00:22:35,288
(Yuriko) Manami-chan.

342
00:22:36,789 --> 00:22:39,726
I was investigating the drugs seized from Oikawa's home...

343
00:22:39,792 --> 00:22:41,227
(Manami) Yes.

344
00:22:41,294 --> 00:22:43,730
(Yuriko's voice) To poison Mr. Erazaki at the pension →

345
00:22:43,796 --> 00:22:47,233
Fingerprints of people other than Oikawa's were detected on the chemicals used.

346
00:22:47,300 --> 00:22:49,802
(Manami) Eh, whose fingerprints are they?

347
00:22:54,240 --> 00:22:56,743
(Yuriko's voice) Kiryu-kun.

348
00:23:00,246 --> 00:23:02,248
(Manami) Huh?
